CENSUS
  Display sector status: population, efficiency, mobility, food.

SYNTAX
  census [<sects>]
  cens   [<sects>]

DESCRIPTION
  Shows a row for every owned sector in the given area.  With no
  argument, shows all sectors you own.

  Column meanings:
    sect    - x,y coordinates and designation letter
    eff     - efficiency 0-100%.  Production requires >=60%
    prd     - 'n' if sector is stopped (won't produce this update)
    mob     - mobility units (used for moving troops/goods)
    uf del  - delivery direction for uw, food  (. none  $ to dist)
    uf dst  - distribution threshold flag for uw, food
    old     - previous owner (if recently conquered)
    civ     - civilians
    mil     - military
    uw      - uncompensated workers
    food    - food stockpile
    work    - % of civilians working (depends on happiness)
    avail   - workforce available for building ships/planes/units
    ter     - territory number (see info realm)
    fall    - radioactive fallout level
    coa     - 1 if this is a coastal sector

EXAMPLE
  census *                  all your sectors
  census 0,0                just the capital
  census -5:5,-5:5          5-sector radius around capital

